The paper proposes a deep learning algorithm for microtubule segmentation in time-lapse images, which involves computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of recurrent attention, which is a technique commonly used in deep learning for natural language processing (NLP) tasks. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of the proposed algorithm in biology, indicating that it may also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.BIO (Computational Biology and Bioinformatics).
